# CompTIA A+ Certification Guide (2025-2026)

## Overview
CompTIA A+ is an entry-level IT certification that validates foundational knowledge of computer hardware, software, and basic networking. It is the first step in most IT career paths.

**Certification Code:** 220-1001 & 220-1002

---

## Duration & Study Timeline
- **Recommended Study Duration:** 2-3 months
- **Study Hours Required:** 150-200 hours
- **Exam Preparation Time:** 4-6 weeks after completing course material

---

## Exam Details

### Exam Duration
- **Core 1 (220-1001):** 90 minutes
- **Core 2 (220-1002):** 90 minutes
- **Total Testing Time:** 180 minutes (3 hours)

### Exam Structure
- **Core 1:** 90 questions (multiple choice, drag-and-drop, hotspot)
- **Core 2:** 90 questions (multiple choice, drag-and-drop, hotspot)
- **Passing Score:** 675/900 (both exams combined)
- **Question Format:** Multiple choice, drag-and-drop, simulation, hotspot

### Exam Fee (2025-2026)
- **Per Exam:** $226 USD
- **Bundle (Both Exams):** $405 USD (savings of ~$47)
- **Retake Fee:** $226 USD per exam
- **VAT/Tax:** May apply based on location

