## Complete Syllabus & Topics

### CORE 1 (220-1001) - 40% of total exam

#### 1. Mobile Devices (15%)
- Laptop/Desktop Hardware Components
  - Motherboard, CPU, RAM, Storage (HDD/SSD)
  - Power supplies, fans, cooling systems
  - Ports and connectors (USB, DisplayPort, HDMI, Thunderbolt)
- Mobile Device Hardware
  - Smartphones and tablets internals
  - Batteries and charging technologies
  - Display technologies (LCD, OLED, AMOLED)
  - Cameras and microphones
- Accessories
  - Styluses, stands, protective cases
  - Docking stations and connectivity solutions
  - Screen protectors and care products

#### 2. Networking (20%)
- Network Concepts
  - OSI Model (7 layers) overview
  - TCP/IP model basics
  - IP addresses (IPv4, IPv6 introduction)
  - DHCP and static IP addressing
  - DNS basics and domain names
- Networking Equipment
  - Routers and switches basics
  - Access points and WiFi standards
  - Modems and gateways
  - Network cables (Cat5e, Cat6, Cat6a, Cat7)
  - Connectors (RJ45, RJ11)
- Wireless Networking
  - WiFi standards (802.11a/b/g/n/ac/ax)
  - WiFi security (WPA2, WPA3)
  - Bluetooth and BLE basics
  - Cellular technologies (3G, 4G, 5G overview)
- Network Tools
  - Ping and ipconfig/ifconfig
  - Command-line networking tools
  - Network testing equipment

#### 3. Hardware (25%)
- Motherboards and Processors
  - Motherboard components and layout
  - CPU types and speeds
  - CPU sockets (LGA, AM5)
  - BIOS/UEFI basics
- RAM and Storage
  - RAM types (DDR4, DDR5)
  - Storage devices (HDD, SSD, NVMe)
  - RAID basics
  - Storage expansion options
- Power Systems
  - Power supplies (PSU ratings, 80+ efficiency)
  - Battery technologies
  - UPS systems
  - Power management
- Cooling Systems
  - Air cooling (fans, heatsinks)
  - Liquid cooling basics
  - Thermal paste and management
- Display Technologies
  - LCD, LED, OLED displays
  - Display resolution and refresh rates
  - Connectors (HDMI, DisplayPort, VGA)

#### 4. Virtualization & Cloud Computing (12%)
- Virtualization Basics
  - Virtual machines (VMs)
  - Hypervisors (Type 1 and Type 2)
  - Resource allocation
  - Virtual networking
- Cloud Service Models
  - IaaS (Infrastructure as a Service)
  - PaaS (Platform as a Service)
  - SaaS (Software as a Service)
- Cloud Deployment Models
  - Public cloud
  - Private cloud
  - Hybrid cloud
  - Community cloud

#### 5. Hardware & Network Troubleshooting (18%)
- Hardware Troubleshooting Methodology
  - Identify the problem
  - Research and document findings
  - Test theories
  - Establish action plan
  - Implement solution
  - Verify and document
- Common Hardware Issues
  - Motherboard failures
  - CPU and RAM problems
  - Storage failures
  - Power supply issues
- Network Troubleshooting
  - No connectivity issues
  - Slow network performance
  - Connection drops
  - IP addressing problems

### CORE 2 (220-1002) - 60% of total exam

#### 1. Operating Systems Installation, Configuration & Upgrade (20%)
- Windows Operating Systems
  - Windows 10 and Windows 11 features
  - Installation methods (clean, upgrade, in-place)
  - Activation and licensing
  - NTFS vs FAT32 file systems
  - User accounts and groups
  - File permissions and ownership
- macOS
  - macOS basics and features
  - Installation and updates
  - File system (APFS)
  - User management
- Linux
  - Linux distribution basics
  - Installation overview
  - Package managers
  - Command-line basics
  - User and group management

#### 2. Operating System Configuration (15%)
- Desktop and Laptop Configuration
  - Display settings and resolution
  - Power settings and sleep modes
  - Network configuration
  - Device driver management
  - Regional and language settings
- Virtual Memory and Paging
  - Virtual memory concepts
  - Page file management
  - Performance implications
- Remote Access
  - Remote Desktop Protocol (RDP)
  - SSH basics
  - VPN connections

#### 3. Security (25%)
- Physical Security
  - Locking devices and cables
  - BIOS/UEFI passwords
  - Biometric locks
  - Environmental controls
- Windows Security Features
  - Windows Defender and antivirus
  - Windows Firewall
  - Windows Update
  - User Account Control (UAC)
  - BitLocker and encryption
- macOS Security
  - FileVault encryption
  - Gatekeeper and security features
  - System Integrity Protection (SIP)
- Linux Security
  - File permissions (chmod, chown)
  - User and group security
  - SELinux and AppArmor basics
- Authentication
  - Passwords and password policies
  - Multi-factor authentication (MFA)
  - Biometrics
  - PIN and pattern locks
- Encryption
  - Symmetric vs asymmetric encryption basics
  - Full disk encryption
  - File-level encryption
  - SSL/TLS concepts
- Network Security
  - Firewalls basics
  - VPN concepts
  - Network segmentation
  - MAC address filtering

#### 4. Software Troubleshooting (27%)
- Common Software Issues
  - Software won't launch
  - Crashes and freezes
  - Slow performance
  - DLL errors
  - Registry errors (Windows)
  - Application conflicts
- Troubleshooting Methodology
  - Identify the problem
  - Research solutions
  - Create action plan
  - Test and implement
  - Document results
  - Follow up
- System Tools & Utilities
  - Task Manager (Windows)
  - Activity Monitor (macOS)
  - System Monitor (Linux)
  - Event Viewer (Windows)
  - Logs and log files
  - System File Checker (SFC)
  - Disk Cleanup utilities
- Malware & Viruses
  - Malware types (viruses, worms, trojans)
  - Ransomware
  - Spyware and adware
  - Removal tools and processes
  - Prevention strategies

#### 5. Operational Procedures (13%)
- Safety and Environmental Concerns
  - ESD (Electrostatic Discharge) prevention
  - Proper lifting and ergonomics
  - Ventilation and airflow
  - Temperature and humidity management
  - Cable management
- IT Professionalism and Communication
  - Professional conduct
  - Customer service skills
  - Documentation standards
  - Privacy and confidentiality
  - Time management
- Backup and Recovery
  - Backup types (full, incremental, differential)
  - Backup locations
  - Recovery procedures
  - Recovery partition
  - System restore
- Disaster Recovery
  - Disaster recovery plans
  - Business continuity
  - Data preservation

